{
    "abstract": "A computational scheme for reasoning about dynamic systems using (causal) probabilistic networks is presented. The scheme is based on the framework of Lauritzen and Spiegel\u00ad halter {1988), and may be viewed as a gen\u00ad eralization of the inference methods of clas\u00ad sical time-series analysis in the sense that it allows description of non-linear, multi\u00ad variate dynamic systems with complex con\u00ad ditional independence structures. Further , the scheme provides a met hod for efficient backward smoothing and possibilities for effi\u00ad cient, approximate forecasting methods. The scheme has been implemented on top of the HUGIN shell.",
